      "citation_id": "[CITATION_4]",
      "span_text": "There has been particular interest in tetrahydrobiopterin biology, because it can be oxidized to dihydrobiopterin by strong oxidants such as peroxynitrite, which will result in eNOS uncoupling, a condition that turns this enzyme from an NO-producing enzyme into a superoxide source.  Oxidative stress and subsequent peroxynitrite formation may in addition disrupt the zinc thiolate cluster and thereby cause eNOS uncoupling."
